  "response": "As of my last update, you can typically find English-dubbed versions of popular films like \"Death Note II: The Last Name\" on a variety of streaming platforms. Here are some places to check:\n\n1. **Netflix:** They often have a selection of popular foreign films, including those dubbed in English.\n\n2. **Amazon Prime Video:** You may find it available for purchase or rent with English dubbing.\n\n3. **Crunchyroll or Funimation:** These services specialize in anime and related media, so they might have a dubbed version available.\n\n4. **Hulu:** Occasionally, they carry a selection of dubbed foreign films.\n\n5. **Apple iTunes/Google Play Store:** You can rent or purchase movies here, often with options for dubbed audio.\n\nRemember to check the availability in your specific region, as licensing agreements can vary. If it's not available on any of these platforms, you might also look for physical media like DVDs or Blu-rays that offer an English dub.",
